        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 11:47PM CDT until June 9 at 12:45AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>SVRMAF

The National Weather Service in Midland has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northern Mitchell County in western Texas...
Scurry County in western Texas...
Eastern Borden County in western Texas...

* Until 1245 AM CDT.

* At 1147 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 7 miles southeast of Lake Alan Henry to near J B
Thomas Reservoir, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Gail Mesonet recorded a wind gust of 67 MPH.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Snyder, Colorado City, Loraine, Fluvanna, Colorado City Airport, J
B Thomas Reservoir, Inadale, Hermleigh, Randalls Corner, Winston
Field, Knapp, Cuthbert, Buford, Dunn, and Ira.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 216 and 228.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
